text: Emil Keres (9 July 1925 - 1 April 2016) was a Hungarian actor and theatre director. He started his career in 1950. He starred in over 100 stage productions. He also appeared in over ten movies, including Twenty Hours (1965). He was awarded the Kossuth Prize in 1965. He was born in Szombathely.
